# ğŸ›‘ Common Mistakes

âŒ Using `==`
âŒ Forgetting falsy values
âŒ Using `||` when 0 is valid
âŒ Confusing prefix/postfix increment
âŒ Ignoring operator precedence

---

# ğŸ¯ Interview Rapid-Fire Summary

* `+` can concatenate or add
* `===` checks value + type
* `&&` returns first falsy
* `||` returns first truthy
* `??` checks only null/undefined
* Prefix vs Postfix matters
* JS has implicit coercion


